South Africa’s annual consumer inflation ticked up to 4.7 percent in December compared with 4.6 percent in November, the national statistics agency said on Wednesday.
Statistics South Africa said the consumer price index increased by 0.5 percent month-on-month in December.
– African News Agency (ANA)
 
